fn.p:
Inhaled dose calculated as: Dose (mg/kg/day) = (C × MV × T)/BW, where C is the test atmosphere concentration (mg/L) per group (first of two daily exposures);


MV is the group mean minute volume for the appropriate sex;



calculated as (L/min) = 0.499 × BW0.809 *;



T is the duration of exposure (60 minutes);



BW is the group mean body weight for the appropriate sex.
